<span id="freeTextContainer8572170543614078154">WHAT JUST HAPPENED. <br/><br/>Okay, before I get into the review, I need to say that I’m not even going to try and avoid spoilers. For those of you who are considering reading this book, know this: There’s really no bad content, and it’s an excellent book. <br/><br/>Now, on to spoilers!<br/><br/>LIKES:<br/>- Parvin. Again. Seriously, her faith and trust in God is so inspiring and beautiful. And her relationships with every character was just so well-written, especially....<br/>- Parvin x Solomon. Guys, I might have found a new OTP. I </span>
  <span id="freeText8572170543614078154" style="display:none">WHAT JUST HAPPENED. <br /><br />Okay, before I get into the review, I need to say that I’m not even going to try and avoid spoilers. For those of you who are considering reading this book, know this: There’s really no bad content, and it’s an excellent book. <br /><br />Now, on to spoilers!<br /><br />LIKES:<br />- Parvin. Again. Seriously, her faith and trust in God is so inspiring and beautiful. And her relationships with every character was just so well-written, especially....<br />- Parvin x Solomon. Guys, I might have found a new OTP. I wasn’t a huge fan of Parvin x Jude, but THIS I can get behind. <br />- The cover. Let’s all take a moment to stare at that piece of artwork.<br /><br />Done? Let’s move on. <br /><br />- The ending. WHAT. I CRIED. (Although, come on, there’s a third book. Guess who’s coming back to life?? ;) )<br /><br />DISLIKES:<br />- I was a little skeptical about why on earth the Council would send them to Antarctica, of all places. So were they trying to kill the Radicals, or just torture them????<br /><br />Overall, this is an absolutely incredible book that will make you cry. Highly recommend this series, guys. READ IT. IT WILL CHANGE YOUR LIFE. </span>
