<div id="review_4399048674" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4399048674" />
    <a title="Kristianne" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/117300451-kristianne"><img alt="Kristianne" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1639993970p2/117300451.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4399048674?book_show_action=true">Dec 19, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kristianne" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kristianne" href="/user/show/117300451-kristianne">Kristianne</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4399048674" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2254857074484896195">This book is definitely my favorite of all three. Solomon and Parvin’s relationship finally came alive and really took off here. And while Parvin did grow and learn more about herself in book one, book two is where she blossomed into the amazing leader she was destined to become. I loved seeing all she’d learned in book one come out in her actions as she sacrificed herself for her people and led them through the wilderness. There were so many parallels to the biblical story that I absolutely lov</span>
  <span id="freeText2254857074484896195" style="display:none">This book is definitely my favorite of all three. Solomon and Parvin’s relationship finally came alive and really took off here. And while Parvin did grow and learn more about herself in book one, book two is where she blossomed into the amazing leader she was destined to become. I loved seeing all she’d learned in book one come out in her actions as she sacrificed herself for her people and led them through the wilderness. There were so many parallels to the biblical story that I absolutely loved. And so many scenes that made me cry because they were heartbreaking yet beautiful. <i>*sobs*</i><br /><br />I never knew what to expect! Nadine is amazing at creating twists and turns you never see coming but make complete sense when you go back.<br /><br />I must mention the romance. <i>*sighs happily*</i> I always love a good friends-to-lovers plot, and I appreciated that Nadine took time to develop their friendship before it grew into something more. Solomon is my favorite love interest EVER. I adored how he went after Parvin and loved her and protected her and cared for her. And yet, even with all those amazing qualities, he was still human. He still made mistakes, which made him all the more endearing.<br /><br />I also loved what an important role family played in the story. Parvin’s struggle with her mom was very relatable, and I love how she worked to restore their relationship despite all the other pressures on her.<br /><br /><a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[My heart broke when Parvin sacrificed herself at the end. It was amazing to watch her grow to that point where she could give herself up for others. And what a powerful picture of what Christ did for us! <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br />All I can say is, you need to read this book! So go do it. Now! (Of course, only after you’ve read book one. ;)</span>
  <a data-text-id="2254857074484896195" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


